{{Use British English|date=July 2015}}
'''William Vaughan''' is a British Art Historian and has been ''Emeritus Professor of History of Art'' at [[Birkbeck College]], [[University of London]] since 2003.<ref>[http://www.bbk.ac.uk/about-us/fellows/william-vaughan Emeritus Professor William Vaughan] Birkbeck College, University of London, 2012. Retrieved 29 October 2012. [https://www.webcitation.org/6BlMr73KT Archived here.]</ref>

He is also a printmaker, and regularly exhibits in London and [[Bristol]] under the name Will Vaughan.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://willvaughan.com|website=Will Vaughan|accessdate=13 January 2016}}</ref> He is Chair of the Bruton Art Society.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.brutonartsociety.co.uk/committee/|website=Bruton Art Society|accessdate=13 January 2016}}</ref>

